        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>This liquid contains blood from a copper dragon. For 1 hour after you imbibe the concoction, you can unleash a copper dragon's breath weapon. The potency of the breath depends on the potion's type, based on the age of the dragon whose blood was used to make the potion.</p>\n<p>Exhaling dragon breath uses a single action. You create a 30-foot line of acid which deals <a class=\"inline-roll roll\" data-mode=\"roll\" data-flavor=\"\" data-formula=\"6d6\" title=\"6d6\"><i class=\"fas fa-dice-d20\"></i> 6d6</a> acid damage. All creatures in the area must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"29\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,magical,potion\" data-pf2-label=\"Adult Copper Dragon's Breath Potion DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save.</p>\n<p>After you use the breath weapon, you can't do so again for <a class=\"inline-roll roll\" data-mode=\"roll\" data-flavor=\"\" data-formula=\"1d4\" title=\"1d4\"><i class=\"fas fa-dice-d20\"></i> 1d4</a> rounds.</p>"
        },
